# System Configuration Rules

## Catalogue Schema (`systems/catalogue.json`)
The catalogue is the master registry of all system maps:
```json
{
  "categories": ["Category A", "Category B"],
  "systems": [
    {
      "id": "my_system",
      "name": "My System Map",
      "description": "A socio-environmental systems map covering...",
      "thumbnail": "my_system/system-image.png",
      "category": "Category A"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Catalogue Fields
| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `categories` | `string[]` | Yes | Sorted list of all categories |
| `systems` | `object[]` | Yes | Array of system entries |
| `systems[].id` | `string` | Yes | URL-safe ID (lowercase, underscores) |
| `systems[].name` | `string` | Yes | Display name |
| `systems[].description` | `string` | Yes | Short description for catalogue cards |
| `systems[].thumbnail` | `string\|null` | No | Relative path from `systems/` to thumbnail |
| `systems[].category` | `string` | Yes | Must exist in `categories` array |

### Rules
1. **IDs must be unique** across all systems
2. **Categories array** must contain all categories referenced by systems
3. **Thumbnail paths** are relative to the `systems/` directory
4. **Keep categories sorted** alphabetically
5. **Clean up categories** — remove categories with no remaining systems

## System Config Schema (`systems/{id}/config.json`)
```json
{
  "id": "my_system",
  "name": "My System",
  "title": "My System Systems Map - Interactive Visualization",
  "description": "A socio-environmental systems map for...",
  "spreadsheets": {
    "main": "GOOGLE_SHEETS_SPREADSHEET_ID",
    "draft": "GOOGLE_SHEETS_SPREADSHEET_ID"
  },
  "apiKey": "GOOGLE_SHEETS_API_KEY",
  "images": {
    "systemImage": { "src": "system-image.png", "alt": "My System" },
    "thumbnail": { "src": "thumbnail.png", "alt": "My System" }
  }
}
```

### Config Fields
| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| `id` | `string` | Yes | Must match the directory name |
| `name` | `string` | Yes | Display name |
| `title` | `string` | Yes | Full page title (format: `{Name} Systems Map - Interactive Visualization`) |
| `description` | `string` | Yes | Description (same as catalogue entry) |
| `spreadsheets.main` | `string` | Yes | Google Sheets ID for the main data source |
| `spreadsheets.draft` | `string` | No | Google Sheets ID for draft version (can be same as main) |
| `apiKey` | `string` | Yes | Google Sheets API key |
| `images.systemImage` | `object` | No | `{src, alt}` for the main system image |
| `images.thumbnail` | `object` | No | `{src, alt}` for the thumbnail |
| `images.logo` | `object\|null` | No | Optional logo image |

### Google Sheets ID
The spreadsheet ID is extracted from Google Sheets URLs:
```
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/SPREADSHEET_ID/edit...
                                       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
```
Only store the ID, not the full URL.

## Adding a New System

### Via API (preferred)
POST to `/api/systems` with:
```json
{
  "id": "my_system",
  "name": "My System",
  "description": "...",
  "category": "My Category",
  "spreadsheets": { "main": "SHEET_ID" },
  "apiKey": "API_KEY",
  "systemImage_base64": "data:image/png;base64,..."
}
```

### Manually
1. Create `systems/my_system/` directory
2. Create `config.json` following the schema above
3. Add `system-image.png` and/or `thumbnail.png` (optional)
4. Update `systems/catalogue.json`:
   - Add system to `systems` array
   - Add category to `categories` if new

## Google Sheets Structure
Each system's spreadsheet MUST have two tabs:

### FACTORS Tab (Columns A–E)
| Col | Header | Required | Format |
|-----|--------|----------|--------|
| A | `factor_id` | Yes | `V1`, `V2`, ... |
| B | `name` | Yes | Display name |
| C | `domain_name` | Yes | Domain category |
| D | `intervenable` | No | `Yes` / `No` |
| E | `definition` | No | Description |

### RELATIONSHIPS Tab (Columns A–I)
| Col | Header | Required | Format |
|-----|--------|----------|--------|
| A | `relationship_id` | No | `R1`, `R2`, ... |
| B | `from` | No | Source name (informational) |
| C | `to` | No | Target name (informational) |
| D | `from_factor_id` | Yes | Must match FACTORS col A |
| E | `to_factor_id` | Yes | Must match FACTORS col A |
| F | `polarity` | No | `same` / `opposite` |
| G | `strength` | No | `strong` / `medium` / `weak` |
| H | `delay` | No | `days` / `months` / `years` |
| I | `definition` | No | Link description |

## Existing Systems
The platform currently hosts several system maps. Check `systems/catalogue.json` for the up-to-date list. Systems can span any domain (e.g., fisheries, water resources, urban planning, climate adaptation). The platform is domain-agnostic — categories and systems are user-defined.

## Important Constraints
1. **Never modify system configs without updating the catalogue** (and vice versa)
2. **System IDs must be filesystem-safe**: `[a-z0-9_-]` only
3. **Spreadsheets must be publicly shared** (Anyone with link → Viewer)
4. **Image paths in config are relative** to the system's own directory
5. **Thumbnail paths in catalogue are relative** to the `systems/` directory
6. **The API key is shared** across all systems (consider this for security)
